title: Gorbiscape agelenoides
text: Gorbiscape agelenoides, <a href="Synonym%20%28taxonomy%29">synonym</a> Agelena agelenoides, is a species of <a href="spider">spider</a> in the family <a href="Agelenidae">Agelenidae</a>, which contains at least 1,350 species . It was first described by Walckenaer in 1842. It is commonly found in the western Mediterranean region.
